{{Infobox Union |name=American Institute for Conservation |affiliation= [[Professional association]] |full_name= American Institute for Conservation of Historic and Artistic Works (AIC) |image= [[File:2016 AIC Logo.jpeg|204px]] |founded= 1972 }} The '''American Institute for Conservation of Historic and Artistic Works''' ('''AIC''') is a national [[membership organization]] of [[Conservation-restoration of cultural heritage|conservation]] professionals, headquartered in [[Washington,_D.C.|Washington D.C.]].
== History == The AIC first launched in 1972 with only a handful of members. Now it is grown to over 3,500 members in over twenty countries around the world.<ref>{{cite web|title=Journal of the American Institute for Conservation|url=http://www.scimagojr.com/journalsearch.php?q=16300154700&tip=sid&clean=0|website=SCImago Journal & Country Rank|accessdate=2 May 2015}}</ref>
== Foundation == The Foundation of the American Institute for Conservation (FAIC) was incorporated in 1972 to support the [[Charity (practice)|charitable]], [[Science|scientific]], and educational activities of the AIC. FAIC primarily manages and provides funds for educational and professional development for the betterment of the conservation profession.{{cn|date=March 2018}}
== Publications and Resources == The AIC publications include ''The Journal of the American Insititure for Conservation'', ''AIC News'', and Specialty Group Publications.
